    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras are looking at a high-ceiling slate today, headlined by **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (77.02) and **Junior Caminero** (76.66). **Pete Crow-Armstrong** is our premier play, benefiting from a high-upside matchup against Tobias Myers and a significant boost from dynamic platoon positioning. Similarly, **Junior Caminero** enters the lineup as an elite utility option; he faces Mitch Keller in conditions bolstered by winds blowing out, adding a +5% efficiency premium that makes him a must-start despite a neutral park factor. While **Carson Benge** (63.27) remains in our starting rotation, he carries a 34% rain risk alongside **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, which bears monitoring as the day progresses. We are also leaning heavily on the power-speed upside of **Trea Turner** (69.15), who leverages his leadoff spot to capitalize against Grant Holmes, balancing out the risk of our catcher platoon.\n\nThe optimizer faced its toughest decision regarding the benching of **Victor Scott II** (47.23). While his elite sprint speed is a cornerstone of our strategy, his projected 9th-order spot creates a massive efficiency drag (-8%) that pushed him below our starting threshold today. He remains our primary pivot should any late-scratch lineup shifts occur. Meanwhile, we are comfortable fading **Colt Keith** (42.13) and **Luke Raley** (37.46) against tough southpaws like Garrett Crochet and MacKenzie Gore, respectively. These benching decisions reflect a disciplined approach to game caps, prioritizing high-efficiency matchups for **Kyle Schwarber** (66.04) and **Yordan Alvarez** (67.90) to ensure we maximize our 5x5 category output against favorable defensive pairings.",
